00:04:23.960 --> 00:04:26.900
A little bit of Joomla
politics or Joomla history.

00:04:27.910 --> 00:04:29.890
Joomla is actually a fork.

00:04:31.430 --> 00:04:38.920
Joomla is a fork of content
management system called Mambo,

00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:43.410
which was really
popular at that point.

00:04:43.410 --> 00:04:47.740
It was developed by an
Australian company called Miro.

00:04:48.750 --> 00:04:56.970
They decided to stop doing it
open source and doing it propriety

00:04:56.970 --> 00:04:59.920
or changing sometimes in the code.

00:04:59.920 --> 00:05:06.980
The core developers of Mambo decided
that it was not the way to go,

00:05:06.980 --> 00:05:14.930
and they created this fork
to have an open-source

00:05:14.930 --> 00:05:18.860
content management system
because that's how they thought

00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:19.970
the web should be.

00:05:21.650 --> 00:05:26.550
Personally, that move was
well, and they even got a name,

00:05:26.550 --> 00:05:33.410
which is the Swahili word Jumla,
which means "all together"

00:05:33.410 --> 00:05:39.810
or "as a whole", it depends on
where you look for the translation.

00:05:39.810 --> 00:05:43.500
I do not speak Swahili,
so I cannot tell you for sure.

00:05:43.500 --> 00:05:47.910
Anyway, to create this
or to make this happen,

00:05:47.910 --> 00:05:50.317
they created a
non-profit organization

00:05:50.317 --> 00:05:53.750
called Open Source Matters.

00:05:53.750 --> 00:06:00.010
This is the legal entity that covers
Joomla in the financial aspects.

00:06:00.010 --> 00:06:08.200
It protects the Joomla copyright, and
also they made some high decisions

00:06:08.200 --> 00:06:14.510
about the structure,
how the project should be doing.

00:06:14.510 --> 00:06:19.920
The board of Open Source Matters
is four by four, is formed

00:06:19.920 --> 00:06:23.880
by four elected members, president,
vice president, treasurer,

00:06:23.880 --> 00:06:31.170
and secretary, and all the
working department leaders

00:06:31.170 --> 00:06:35.900
of the different working
structure of Joomla.

00:06:35.900 --> 00:06:39.470
We have different
departments for events.

00:06:39.470 --> 00:06:44.760
We have a department for production,
that is mainly the core of the code.

00:06:44.760 --> 00:06:48.160
We have a department for marketing.

00:06:48.160 --> 00:06:49.720
We have several departments.

00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:50.950
Okay.

00:06:50.950 --> 00:06:53.360
Then every leader of
these departments,

00:06:55.200 --> 00:06:57.780
from the Open Source Matters board.

00:06:57.780 --> 00:07:02.390
Also, the departments are
splitted or are divided in teams.

00:07:02.390 --> 00:07:05.500
For instance, the Joomla
accessibility team is part

00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:11.390
of the production department.

00:07:11.390 --> 00:07:14.590
A little bit of Joomla wants.

00:07:14.590 --> 00:07:18.550
What you can see here
if you have a screen

00:07:18.550 --> 00:07:23.840
or you can see my slides,
is the Joomla backend

00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:29.570
because in Joomla we have
two different applications.

00:07:30.810 --> 00:07:35.980
We have the Joomla administrator,
which is what they called backend,

00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:42.420
and it's independent from
what visitors of the site see,

00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:45.080
that is the Joomla front.

00:07:45.080 --> 00:07:48.600
We call it front.

00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:54.600
In this talk, I will try to
name Joomla administrator,

00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:59.610
but at some point, I might say
Joomla backend, so sorry for that.

00:07:59.610 --> 00:08:04.610
In Joomla,
we also have plugins and widgets.

00:08:05.830 --> 00:08:11.590
We call plugins, plugins, but for
widgets, we use the word modules.

00:08:13.120 --> 00:08:15.220
We also have themes.

00:08:15.220 --> 00:08:21.250
For themes we use the word templates,
but basically it's the same.

00:08:23.190 --> 00:08:27.980
In Joomla,
we have a concept which is override.

00:08:27.980 --> 00:08:33.390
It's a very
programming-minded concept.

00:08:33.390 --> 00:08:39.700
It means that no matter what a
plugin gives you in the front end,

00:08:39.700 --> 00:08:46.890
in the view, you can change it using
a specific path to put your changes,

00:08:46.890 --> 00:08:50.980
and then it change the output.

00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:56.070
You can replace what the developer
have in mind with your own code,

00:08:56.070 --> 00:08:57.020
and it will work.

00:08:57.020 --> 00:09:00.210
It's just for aesthetics.

00:09:00.210 --> 00:09:03.580
It's just for the structure,
VH domain structure, and the CSS

00:09:03.580 --> 00:09:09.750
of what people see.

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:15.350
Joomla is also fully featured
with interesting extensions.

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:21.380
The Joomla code has
probably everything you need

00:09:21.380 --> 00:09:26.320
to create a website,
a corporate website

00:09:26.320 --> 00:09:30.780
with no third-party extensions,
no third-party plugins.

00:09:30.780 --> 00:09:35.200
Just with Joomla,
you can develop a great website.

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:40.260
We actually had last month,
a challenge in our marquee,

00:09:41.540 --> 00:09:47.470
which was how to build a
website just using Joomla code,

00:09:47.470 --> 00:09:51.930
without any third-party plugins.

00:09:53.180 --> 00:09:58.750
It's something you can do and you can
do great things just using Joomla,

00:09:58.750 --> 00:09:59.820
what Joomla provides.

00:10:01.270 --> 00:10:08.840
Anyway, even so, we also have
components or different extensions,

00:10:08.840 --> 00:10:11.200
components, libraries, plugins.

00:10:11.200 --> 00:10:16.260
We have third parties and other
developers that provide plugins

00:10:16.260 --> 00:10:18.480
to Joomla to make it rich.

00:10:22.770 --> 00:10:26.610
Since the beginning, Joomla
has had accessibility in mind.

00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:30.890
Actually, I was surprised when
I started learning about this

00:10:30.890 --> 00:10:34.290
because I have been involved in
Joomla, have been using Joomla

00:10:34.290 --> 00:10:40.410
since Mambo times, but when you
were not aware of accessibility

00:10:40.410 --> 00:10:46.890
or all the aspects, you do not
pay that much attention to them.

00:10:46.890 --> 00:10:53.140
Actually, when Joomla splitted from
Mambo, when Joomla was started,

00:10:53.140 --> 00:10:57.810
it was basically Mambo
code and it was Joomla 1.0

00:10:57.810 --> 00:11:02.970
and there was not that much
accessibility features.

00:11:02.970 --> 00:11:05.800
Just the ones that
were in core Mambo.

00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:13.160
The first release, you can consider
a Joomla, 100% Joomla, more or less.

00:11:13.160 --> 00:11:20.500
Is the Joomla 1.5 release and that
release in the Joomla framework,

00:11:20.500 --> 00:11:24.470
another aspect of Joomla.

00:11:24.470 --> 00:11:30.850
It also came with one template,
one theme called Beez.

00:11:32.410 --> 00:11:43.030
This theme was a fully
accessible theme.

00:11:44.140 --> 00:11:47.190
It also came with a
couple of extra themes,

00:11:47.190 --> 00:11:52.490
but this one is interesting because
it was a fully accessible theme

00:11:52.490 --> 00:11:55.150
by the standards we
had at that moment.

00:11:56.680 --> 00:11:58.550
Interesting features it had.

00:11:58.550 --> 00:12:01.550
It provided a font size selector.

00:12:01.550 --> 00:12:03.400
It had very good contrast.

00:12:04.700 --> 00:12:12.880
At that point Joomla 1.5, 2008,
Joomla was showing all the code

00:12:12.880 --> 00:12:17.340
or creating HTML code still
with some tables in it.

00:12:17.340 --> 00:12:21.870
Our team developers were still
showing tables to a structure

00:12:21.870 --> 00:12:29.140
to lay out the content,
but the Beez theme had no tables.

00:12:29.140 --> 00:12:33.090
It was a fully or very
nice great template.

00:12:34.220 --> 00:12:42.070
In my opinion,
Beez has one problem that made it,

00:12:42.070 --> 00:12:44.870
not everyone like it
or not everyone use it.

00:12:44.870 --> 00:12:48.250
It was a very student design.

00:12:48.250 --> 00:12:53.780
It was a very pinky, very violent
purple theme with some bees

00:12:53.780 --> 00:12:56.040
that were very nice than cartoons.

00:12:58.220 --> 00:13:04.220
That makes people thought, this is
not a serious option for my website.

00:13:04.220 --> 00:13:08.810
Especially, it was a time where
everyone wanted a corporate website

00:13:08.810 --> 00:13:13.710
that was great to sell or to
tell how good your company was.

00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:18.970
This was not the best template
for that because of this design

00:13:18.970 --> 00:13:24.370
that made some people thought
it was not a serious proposal.

00:13:24.370 --> 00:13:30.700
Anyway, those developers who were
aware of the accessibility features

00:13:30.700 --> 00:13:36.670
in Beez who really had access
reading mind when developing website

00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:41.150
still kept using it.

00:13:41.150 --> 00:13:48.294
I can tell you that one of
the judicial systems website

00:13:48.294 --> 00:13:50.613
in Australia,
I don't remember exactly

00:13:50.613 --> 00:13:55.960
which ones had
exactly this template,

00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:57.350
this theme installed.

00:13:59.300 --> 00:14:02.920
You could recognize some of
the layouts on the features,

00:14:02.920 --> 00:14:06.700
but obviously, it has a more
server option for columns,

00:14:06.700 --> 00:14:09.690
that was so pinky.

00:14:09.690 --> 00:14:17.030
It was interesting in that
sense, so people could use it

00:14:17.030 --> 00:14:19.540
even though it was so sustained.

00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:25.440
One interesting thing about
this team is, it was blacked

00:14:25.440 --> 00:14:29.960
with overrides like it over-ridded
everything to make it accessible.

00:14:29.960 --> 00:14:35.290
It was also a good experiment
for theme developers

00:14:35.290 --> 00:14:38.940
to create their own
versions of software.

00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:46.790
Anyway, as I mentioned, it was not
the most popular theme for Joomla.

00:14:46.790 --> 00:14:49.500
After Joomla 1.5,
we got Joomla 2.5 and Joomla 3,

00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:55.070
and those two releases came
with Beez 2 and Beez 3.

00:14:56.100 --> 00:15:00.563
These Beez themes
still were accessible,

00:15:00.563 --> 00:15:08.107
still were a nice templates, nice
themes in the sense of accessibility,

00:15:08.587 --> 00:15:11.900
but they were more boring.

00:15:13.560 --> 00:15:18.510
They abandoned the pinky theme,
the pink colors, the string colors,

00:15:19.620 --> 00:15:22.670
and it they made them more sober.

00:15:24.530 --> 00:15:30.210
Anyway, they were at that
point, really had

00:15:30.210 --> 00:15:36.450
a really strong internal efforts in
Joomla to be compliant with ATAG 2.0.

00:15:39.870 --> 00:15:46.080
Some people in the UX team, like
Angie Radtke, which was a developer

00:15:46.080 --> 00:15:50.180
of the big templates, were
really pushing for accessibility.

00:15:54.120 --> 00:15:58.270
One thing I have to mention
about Joomla historically is that

00:15:58.270 --> 00:16:02.890
even though it was an open-source
system since the beginning,

00:16:02.890 --> 00:16:08.560
and actually the reason
we have Joomla today is

00:16:08.560 --> 00:16:13.010
because the developers really
wanted it to be open-source.

00:16:14.300 --> 00:16:18.670
Historically, it's not being
easy to send changes to Joomla.

00:16:18.670 --> 00:16:24.060
People who have tried or who
tried contributing the early 2000

00:16:24.060 --> 00:16:30.760
at the beginning of the
century, were not very welcome

00:16:30.760 --> 00:16:33.090
to make changes to the code.

00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:39.000
Only the code team in Joomla were
able to make changes to the CMS.

00:16:40.220 --> 00:16:43.430
We're still using SVN.

00:16:43.430 --> 00:16:46.020
It was not easy.

00:16:46.020 --> 00:16:49.690
We had some communications, you
could propose changes, but you have

00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:51.000
to send them by email.

00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:57.460
It was not like a very good way
of getting new contributions

00:16:57.460 --> 00:17:02.110
to the project.

00:17:02.110 --> 00:17:09.460
There were in a case some changes
in the project and at some point,

00:17:09.460 --> 00:17:10.930
they decided to change that.

00:17:12.390 --> 00:17:13.480
We moved to GitHub.

00:17:15.500 --> 00:17:23.050
Now everyone, every user of the
internet, can submit approve requests

00:17:23.050 --> 00:17:27.850
and if it's good enough or it has
no problems, it solves an issue

00:17:29.100 --> 00:17:35.240
and it's tested correctly,
it can be incorporated into Joomla.

00:17:35.240 --> 00:17:38.230
There's no issue for that.

00:17:38.230 --> 00:17:44.160
Right now, the Joomla production
team keeps checking all the code

00:17:44.160 --> 00:17:48.690
that is submitted into
Joomla, but it's much easier

00:17:48.690 --> 00:17:54.660
to get your changes
into the project.

00:17:54.660 --> 00:18:00.740
Also, this came with lots
of changes in the project.

00:18:00.740 --> 00:18:09.021
We have lots of politics,
political changes.

00:18:15.410 --> 00:18:20.000
At some point,
we started to think about Joomla 4.

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:26.940
I say, at some point, because Joomla
4 has been in development since 2013.

00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:32.540
This has been huge.

00:18:32.540 --> 00:18:38.720
I mean, it's been like more than
eight years working in Joomla 4.

00:18:38.720 --> 00:18:48.540
It means that lots of things you
plant in 2013 did not even make it

00:18:48.540 --> 00:18:50.540
to 2016.

00:18:50.540 --> 00:18:56.000
It's like, the standard changes,
you know how the [inaudible]

00:18:56.000 --> 00:18:57.000
is.

00:18:57.850 --> 00:19:03.620
It's like, everything was moved
and we changed lots of things.

00:19:03.620 --> 00:19:07.480
We made different
template, different themes.

00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:11.710
We made lots of change.

00:19:11.710 --> 00:19:17.050
In all this process since
2013, we changed the structure,

00:19:17.050 --> 00:19:18.680
the political structure in Joomla.

00:19:20.410 --> 00:19:25.728
We established the Joomla
accessibility theme was created

00:19:25.729 --> 00:19:27.500
in 2016.

00:19:28.870 --> 00:19:36.050
Since 2005 to 2016, we did not
have any accessibility theme

00:19:36.050 --> 00:19:41.600
or anyone in charge of checking
accessibility into the project.

00:19:41.600 --> 00:19:46.440
We only had volunteers who
wanted it to be accessible

00:19:46.440 --> 00:19:49.940
but we didn't have an accessibility
team or a team dedicated

00:19:49.940 --> 00:19:50.940
to accessibility.

00:19:54.180 --> 00:20:03.080
Since 2016 till 2019, the new
created accessibility team made

00:20:03.080 --> 00:20:09.150
a huge effort in generating lots
of documentation and raising issues

00:20:09.150 --> 00:20:14.920
for the new themes we were developing
for Joomla 4 and participating

00:20:14.920 --> 00:20:20.760
in some decisions we made.

00:20:20.760 --> 00:20:25.570
Before talking about hard decisions
we made, I forgot to mention

00:20:27.190 --> 00:20:32.560
in the introduction that Joomla had
several themes for the front end,

00:20:32.560 --> 00:20:34.680
and one of them was Beez.

00:20:34.680 --> 00:20:37.650
We have talked a lot about Beez.

00:20:39.630 --> 00:20:43.700
For the back-end, for Joomla
administrator, we also have themes

00:20:44.780 --> 00:20:47.650
and we have the history gallery.

00:20:47.650 --> 00:20:51.290
We have had at least two themes
for the Joomla administrator.

00:20:53.600 --> 00:20:59.680
One is the default one,
which was not created or developed

00:20:59.680 --> 00:21:01.250
with accessibility in mind.

00:21:01.250 --> 00:21:05.480
The other one, which was a
simplified version of the first one,

00:21:06.552 --> 00:21:15.972
which was not fully accessible, but
we like it to think it was accessible

00:21:15.980 --> 00:21:17.080
because it was simpler.

00:21:19.170 --> 00:21:23.410
Anyway, it was like
what we thought we had

00:21:23.410 --> 00:21:26.250
or why we had that
theme in Joomla 4.

00:21:26.250 --> 00:21:31.970
In Joomla 4, we did some decisions,
which some of them were harder

00:21:31.970 --> 00:21:38.190
because it meant to put lots of
people in the same direction,

00:21:38.190 --> 00:21:41.110
but I think we were
the correct one.

00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:44.900
First of all,
we do not need an accessible theme.

00:21:46.040 --> 00:21:50.300
We do not need an accessible theme
for the Joomla administrator,

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:54.480
and we do not need an accessible
theme for the public path

00:21:54.480 --> 00:21:56.920
or as a default theme.

00:21:58.010 --> 00:22:06.630
We need the one administrator
theme we release

00:22:06.630 --> 00:22:11.220
and the one front-end theme
we released at accessible.

00:22:11.220 --> 00:22:16.200
We did not need two themes,
so people can choose if they want

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:19.130
to be accessible or if they
like the other designs.

00:22:20.210 --> 00:22:25.900
We need everything that is developed
in Joomla to be accessible.

00:22:27.090 --> 00:22:30.660
That was the first decision.

00:22:30.660 --> 00:22:34.520
We worked through having just
one theme for the back end

00:22:34.520 --> 00:22:41.727
and one theme for the front end, and
both of them have got accessibility.

00:22:44.090 --> 00:22:51.990
Both administrator and front-end
themes are right now accessible.

00:22:51.990 --> 00:22:59.360
We made them compliant
with the WCAG 2.1 level AA.

00:23:01.540 --> 00:23:10.600
We made it making designers
UX experts to work together

00:23:10.600 --> 00:23:14.880
with accessibility members, raising
out their accessibility issues.

00:23:14.880 --> 00:23:20.350
This has not been a work of
the accessibility team alone.

00:23:20.350 --> 00:23:25.280
We have the great
contributions in the community.

00:23:26.740 --> 00:23:33.620
That we can have both themes,
back-end and front-end,

00:23:33.620 --> 00:23:36.950
accessible in the
higher standards we set.

00:23:37.960 --> 00:23:42.800
We also added some
features for Joomla 4,

00:23:42.800 --> 00:23:48.280
like a accessibility settings so
that when people have an account

00:23:48.280 --> 00:23:52.820
in your site, they can decide
if they want to see the site

00:23:52.820 --> 00:23:58.500
in monochrome, if they want a
bigger font size, a higher contrast,

00:23:58.500 --> 00:24:02.770
or highlight the
links, all the links.

00:24:02.770 --> 00:24:06.110
That is a decision they made
in their account settings.

00:24:07.310 --> 00:24:10.840
They just log in and we have
all the settings they want.

00:24:12.380 --> 00:24:18.100
We also have some nice plugins
like the skip to links.

00:24:18.100 --> 00:24:22.640
This plugin allows you
the skip to button.

00:24:22.640 --> 00:24:27.440
When you are navigating
a Joomla 4 website

00:24:27.440 --> 00:24:33.810
and you click the tabular
key, the Tab key, you see,

00:24:33.810 --> 00:24:39.010
I skip to menu that automatically
detects the structure of your page,

00:24:39.010 --> 00:24:46.670
your landmarks, and allows you to
jump to the landmark you choose.

00:24:47.730 --> 00:24:53.590
Also, one thing that is funny,
we packed Joomla 4 with an overlay.

00:24:55.060 --> 00:25:00.030
I know they are very controversial,
and today we agree overlays

00:25:00.030 --> 00:25:05.250
are not the need or what
sort of accessibility.

00:25:05.250 --> 00:25:11.190
We also thought that overlays
can help in some cases

00:25:11.190 --> 00:25:20.070
where users do not have the
required ability to manage a website

00:25:21.340 --> 00:25:25.060
or to manage the accessibility
settings in their browser or they are

00:25:25.060 --> 00:25:26.750
in a different browser.

00:25:26.750 --> 00:25:31.580
Maybe overlays can help at
some point to some users.

00:25:31.580 --> 00:25:35.550
We packed Joomla with this
overlay plugin, which is optional,

00:25:35.550 --> 00:25:40.900
and we actually discourage
people to use it as a replacement

00:25:40.900 --> 00:25:44.380
for our fully accessible website.

00:25:44.380 --> 00:25:47.680
I guess, we think it
might be useful as well.

00:25:50.020 --> 00:25:58.625
Also, another thing we have
accomplished in Joomla 4

00:25:58.625 --> 00:26:04.063
is that right now,
Joomla confirms ATAG 2.0.

00:26:05.440 --> 00:26:10.590
We have made easier for people
to develop accessible content.

00:26:10.590 --> 00:26:17.400
We have paid high attention
to images when you need

00:26:17.400 --> 00:26:22.370
to use alt descriptions.

00:26:24.420 --> 00:26:29.450
We have made alt description of
choice a real choice for people

00:26:29.450 --> 00:26:32.130
so that they need
to specifically say,

00:26:32.130 --> 00:26:35.960
"No, we do not need another
description for this image."

00:26:35.960 --> 00:26:38.790
If they do not provide
an alt description,

00:26:38.790 --> 00:26:46.540
and they do not say that they need
another description, they need

00:26:46.540 --> 00:26:47.890
to add another description.

00:26:47.890 --> 00:26:54.310
It's like, we are trying to make
it easier for content directors

00:26:54.310 --> 00:26:57.940
to have a more accessible website.

00:26:57.940 --> 00:27:02.730
Joomla 4 is packed
with TinyMCE editor.

00:27:04.500 --> 00:27:10.550
We have added some nice features
to make it more accessible.

00:27:11.920 --> 00:27:14.750
Finally, we have a fork.

00:27:14.750 --> 00:27:23.100
A couple of plugins in GitHub to
provide an accessibility test there.

00:27:23.100 --> 00:27:27.590
Right now in Joomla when you are
writing a post, you can click

00:27:27.590 --> 00:27:31.490
on test accessibility
button, and then you will see

00:27:31.490 --> 00:27:35.660
