00:28:50.610 --> 00:28:57.520
It's like very few people
try to add their own designs

00:28:57.520 --> 00:29:02.570
because Joomla provides
with an easy-to-use way

00:29:02.571 --> 00:29:03.680
to create their views.

00:29:04.700 --> 00:29:08.650
They do not need to
create their own views.

00:29:10.710 --> 00:29:17.540
Even though we are trying to
help or to be to ensure that

00:29:17.540 --> 00:29:23.560
when people add new features into
Joomla, these are accessible.

00:29:24.610 --> 00:29:29.750
We want to keep doing improvements
in the way people create content

00:29:31.260 --> 00:29:32.780
in Joomla.

00:29:32.780 --> 00:29:37.550
Recently, we have created
a new user experience team.

00:29:38.720 --> 00:29:42.400
We have a tight connection
between this team

00:29:42.400 --> 00:29:45.370
and the Joomla accessibility
team so that we can--

00:29:47.350 --> 00:29:50.630
I think from my point of
view, user experience

00:29:50.630 --> 00:29:57.590
and accessibility is probably
two sides of the same coin.

00:29:57.590 --> 00:30:04.800
You just want people to use your
website in the best way possible.

00:30:04.800 --> 00:30:10.500
It makes lots of sense to
have a tight relationship

00:30:10.500 --> 00:30:14.513
between this user experience
team and the accessibility team.

00:30:16.366 --> 00:30:30.590
We are committed to develop
lots of documentation, focus on

00:30:30.590 --> 00:30:34.530
how to make Joomla or the
content we create for Joomla

00:30:34.530 --> 00:30:38.060
