Let's check another one.

00:42:57.480 --> 00:43:02.280
Link text may not be descriptive
enough out of the context.

00:43:02.280 --> 00:43:05.920
Learn more link here
is also an issue.

00:43:05.920 --> 00:43:10.270
We might have one creating
this content like this.

00:43:10.270 --> 00:43:16.340
The H4 in this content,
nonconsecutive heading level used.

00:43:16.340 --> 00:43:20.298
Headings should never skip levels
or go from Heading 2 to Heading 4.

00:43:25.157 --> 00:43:29.590
You can configure this to be
shown only to author so people

00:43:29.590 --> 00:43:32.900
with high permissions on your site.

00:43:34.580 --> 00:43:40.680
You can even set some
configuration directly

00:43:40.680 --> 00:43:43.810
from the link test like
checking for the contrast.

00:43:43.810 --> 00:43:45.740
Then we have here a contrast issue.

00:43:45.740 --> 00:43:50.000
You can also check the form levels.

00:43:50.000 --> 00:43:55.070
I don't think we
have any form here.

00:43:55.070 --> 00:44:00.860
You can check for three-level CA's
performance or for readability.

00:44:00.860 --> 00:44:05.490
Finally, [inaudible].

00:44:05.490 --> 00:44:09.370
Basically,
the checker checks the whole page.

00:44:11.190 --> 00:44:14.730
You can't even use it when
you are not in your articles.

00:44:14.730 --> 00:44:18.210
It's like you can't even check
a development you are doing

00:44:18.210 --> 00:44:20.800
at a website that is
not about a [inaudible].

00:44:20.800 --> 00:44:23.540
You're just creating
a corporative website.

00:44:23.540 --> 00:44:26.250
You can't use Joally to
test the accessibility

00:44:26.250 --> 00:44:30.001
or at least the basic automated
accessibility that they can provide.

00:44:32.020 --> 00:44:32.900
That's it, I guess.

00:44:32.900 --> 00:44:34.180
>> KIM: That's great.

00:44:34.180 --> 00:44:37.350
I think Amber was curious whether
it was a developer-focused tool

00:44:37.350 --> 00:44:40.630
or for the content creators and I
think we can see in this example,

00:44:40.630 --> 00:44:43.290
it's mostly for the
content creators.

00:44:43.290 --> 00:44:44.510
We have a follow-up question.

00:44:46.260 --> 00:44:49.280
As a Joomla community,
I think there are still extensions,

00:44:49.280 --> 00:44:52.210
almost like our plugin
repository with WordPress.

00:44:52.210 --> 00:44:56.610
How do you provide documentation
or any testing for the plugins

00:44:56.610 --> 00:44:58.670
and extensions that
are made for Joomla?

00:44:58.670 --> 00:45:01.990
How do you enforce that
and maintain the standard?

00:45:05.002 --> 00:45:06.450
>> CARLOS: Simply we, we cannot.

00:45:08.820 --> 00:45:15.700
It's not that we do not want, we
have made some checks about testing.

00:45:15.700 --> 00:45:19.120
Well, let me go the whole process.

00:45:19.120 --> 00:45:22.150
In Joomla,
we have these extensions repository.

00:45:23.470 --> 00:45:29.350
It is the Joomla extensions
directory where the users can share

00:45:29.350 --> 00:45:33.920
or submit their plugins
or their extensions.

00:45:41.000 --> 00:45:43.720
This does not host the page.

00:45:44.740 --> 00:45:47.580
This is just advertisement.

00:45:47.580 --> 00:45:51.090
It's just a directory who
links to the page of the offer.

00:45:52.890 --> 00:45:59.280
You do not download them from Joomla,
you download from the alpha page.

00:45:59.280 --> 00:46:07.460
This is just like an "advertisement"
for these extensions.

00:46:07.460 --> 00:46:10.790
It's like you need an extension
and you can't find here

00:46:10.790 --> 00:46:14.060
whatever you need and then
you check with the alpha.

00:46:14.060 --> 00:46:17.860
Any case, every extensions
in this directory need to be

00:46:17.860 --> 00:46:24.130
or must be free software compatible
with GPL, exactly as you do

00:46:24.130 --> 00:46:25.470
in WordPress.

00:46:25.470 --> 00:46:28.540
In WordPress,
I think you have high requirements

00:46:28.540 --> 00:46:36.320
because you also need the
developer to upload the plugin

00:46:36.320 --> 00:46:39.900
to the SVN or to your
SVN and other stuff.

00:46:39.900 --> 00:46:41.740
In Joomla, we do not do that.

00:46:41.740 --> 00:46:46.930
We do check that the plugin is GPL.

00:46:46.930 --> 00:46:53.210
Also, we do some basic tests,
most of them are automated.

00:46:54.970 --> 00:46:59.850
This test checks
for basic security.

00:46:59.850 --> 00:47:05.020
We check that the extensions
do not load external content

00:47:05.020 --> 00:47:08.330
without checking that.

00:47:08.330 --> 00:47:13.260
We do some basic checks,
but we cannot check accessibility

00:47:13.260 --> 00:47:16.640
because as you know
accessibility is not something

00:47:16.640 --> 00:47:19.300
you can test automatically.

00:47:19.300 --> 00:47:20.300
We have some plans.

00:47:20.300 --> 00:47:27.090
We have some ideas of introducing
Joally into the testing process.

00:47:27.090 --> 00:47:33.910
We could use Joally to test
the extensions and the result

00:47:33.910 --> 00:47:35.330
of the extensions.

00:47:35.330 --> 00:47:39.340
The problem with these
Joomla extensions is that

00:47:39.340 --> 00:47:44.660
some of them are very very
complex and they generate lots

00:47:44.660 --> 00:47:46.390
of different views.

00:47:46.390 --> 00:47:48.940
It's not so easy to check.

00:47:48.940 --> 00:47:51.380
We are discussing
how we could make it

00:47:51.380 --> 00:48:01.500
so that people can provide some
extension or some accessibility

00:48:01.500 --> 00:48:04.260
that manifests or declaration.

00:48:04.260 --> 00:48:07.100
We do not have a theme directory.

00:48:07.100 --> 00:48:11.680
I think WordPress have a theme
directory, but we do not have it.

00:48:12.750 --> 00:48:15.950
In that sense, that is
probably the most critical part

00:48:15.950 --> 00:48:17.600
regarding accessibility.

00:48:17.600 --> 00:48:19.260
We cannot check.

00:48:20.264 --> 00:48:21.540
I guess that is.

00:48:22.618 --> 00:48:23.708
Thank you.

00:48:23.920 --> 00:48:24.840
>> KIM: No, totally.

00:48:24.840 --> 00:48:28.560
I would think that the community's
focus on accessibility,

00:48:28.560 --> 00:48:32.480
in general, might imply that
the extensions themselves carry

00:48:32.480 --> 00:48:36.300
through that same spirit and focus.

00:48:36.300 --> 00:48:40.490
To that end, could you speak to
how the focus on accessibility

00:48:40.490 --> 00:48:43.060
from Joomla from
such an early start?

00:48:43.060 --> 00:48:45.000
You said that it's
always been a focus.

00:48:45.000 --> 00:48:47.690
How do you think that's
contributed to the success

00:48:47.690 --> 00:48:50.720
and the public opinion of the CMS?

00:48:52.807 --> 00:48:59.190
>> CARLOS: Well, to be
honest, my impression

00:48:59.190 --> 00:49:05.720
about how accessibility has helped
Joomla historical is not that much

00:49:05.720 --> 00:49:10.100
because I don't think people
or developers were interested

00:49:10.100 --> 00:49:11.510
in accessibility.

00:49:11.510 --> 00:49:15.453
For me,
those involved in accessibility

00:49:15.453 --> 00:49:19.860
in Joomla since 2005 are heroes,

00:49:19.860 --> 00:49:24.410
are complete heroes because they
were fighting against the sea

00:49:24.410 --> 00:49:28.060
and against everything
that was there.

00:49:28.060 --> 00:49:31.030
For me, they are real heroes.

00:49:34.330 --> 00:49:41.340
I think at that moment, it was
something extra that you Joomla had

00:49:41.340 --> 00:49:50.020
and some people who were developing
websites for public institutions

00:49:50.020 --> 00:49:52.310
or public organizations,
they might need it.

00:49:52.310 --> 00:49:54.880
Then they started
looking into that.

00:49:54.880 --> 00:49:59.080
There are some theme providers
for Joomla that are focused,

00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:04.650
or they have some accessible
themes and that is great,

00:50:04.650 --> 00:50:07.430
but there are some, not that many.

00:50:07.430 --> 00:50:12.900
It's a bitty, but commercially, I
don't think accessibility has helped

00:50:12.900 --> 00:50:13.940
in any sense.

00:50:15.470 --> 00:50:22.840
Said so, I think that right
now accessibility is in focus.

00:50:22.840 --> 00:50:27.530
I mean,
we have big organizations like WC

00:50:27.530 --> 00:50:32.270
and all these accessibility
organizations are working

00:50:32.270 --> 00:50:34.580
so that the web is more accessible.

00:50:36.420 --> 00:50:43.350
Every month we have an accessibility
legal case where someone has

00:50:43.350 --> 00:50:47.410
to pay lots of money because
their website was not accessible.

00:50:47.410 --> 00:50:54.930
I hope that accessibility is
something that we can demand

00:50:54.930 --> 00:50:58.778
for everyone in the future
and obviously for Joomla

00:50:58.778 --> 00:51:02.560
and for WordPress and Drupal and
PrestaShop and all this stuff.

00:51:04.695 --> 00:51:05.340
>> KIM: I love that.

00:51:05.340 --> 00:51:06.230
I love that.

